<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,342,151,177]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Etymology:</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin “ 
<taxonomicName box="[878,1001,152,178]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Notiocoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lingulatus">lingulatus</taxonomicName>
”, meaning tongue-shaped, and refers to the tongue-shaped atrial scape; adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,327,231,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[335,621,232,257]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Notiocoelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lingulatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[335,621,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Notiocoelotes lingulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[629,723,231,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[629,723,231,257]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[856,1032,232,257]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Coelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palinitropus">
<emphasis box="[856,1032,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">N. palinitropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Hainan, 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1274,232,258]" name="China" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">China</collectingCountry>
in having the strongly folded copulatory ducts and the small spermathecal heads but can be easily distinguished by the short, square-shaped atrium and the distinctly separated, semi-circular copulatory ducts (
<figureCitation box="[1196,1318,312,338]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 9 – 10" captionStart-1="FIGURES 11 – 13" captionStartId-0="6.[151,269,623,647]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,269,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox-0="[241,1355,186,586]" captionTargetBox-1="[201,1434,722,1068]" captionTargetId-0="figure@6.[218,1370,156,600]" captionTargetId-1="figure@6.[151,1436,722,1068]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 9 – 10. Notiocoelotes lingulatus sp. nov., holotype female from Diaoluoshan Mt., Hainan, China. 9 Epigynum, ventral view; 10 Vulva, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 11 – 13. Notiocoelotes lingulatus sp. nov., holotype female from Diaoluoshan Mt., Hainan, China. 11 Epigynum, ventral view; 12 Vulva, dorsal view; 13 Eyes, fronto-dorsal view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/183477/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/183478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[1256,1318,312,338]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12</number>
</figureCitation>
), whereas 
<taxonomicName box="[151,327,352,377]" class="Arachnida" family="Amaurobiidae" genus="Coelotes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palinitropus">
<emphasis box="[151,327,352,377]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">N. palinitropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a strongly elongated atrium and large, fused, anteriorly extending copulatory ducts.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,780]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,352,391,417]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Description:</emphasis>
Female 
<typeStatus box="[459,566,392,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">holotype</typeStatus>
: Small sized coelotine, total length 
<number box="[1000,1055,392,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.2">4.20</number>
. Dorsal shield of prosoma 
<number box="[1385,1436,392,418]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.9">1.90</number>
long, 
<number box="[218,269,432,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.4">1.40</number>
wide; opisthosoma 
<number box="[504,556,432,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.3">2.30</number>
long, 
<number box="[629,680,432,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.65">1.65</number>
wide (
<figureCitation box="[760,897,432,458]" captionStart="FIGURES 14 – 16" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1656,1680]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,1204,1632]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[218,1370,1204,1633]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14 – 16. Notiocoelotes lingulatus sp. nov., holotype female from Diaoluoshan Mt., Hainan, China, habitus (14 dorsal, 15 lateral, 16 ventral view)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/183479/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[819,897,432,458]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="15.0" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="14.0">14–16</number>
</figureCitation>
). Eye sizes and interdistances: AME smallest, approximately half the size of other eyes which are subequal and clustered (AME 
<number box="[1119,1173,472,498]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.06">0.06</number>
, ALE 
<number box="[1251,1305,472,498]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.1">0.10</number>
, PLE 
<number box="[1377,1431,472,498]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.12">0.12</number>
, PME 
<number box="[220,276,512,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="0.12">0.12</number>
); AME–PME separated by approximately PME diameter (
<figureCitation box="[975,1063,512,538]" captionStart="FIGURES 11 – 13" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[201,1434,722,1068]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1436,722,1068]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 11 – 13. Notiocoelotes lingulatus sp. nov., holotype female from Diaoluoshan Mt., Hainan, China. 11 Epigynum, ventral view; 12 Vulva, dorsal view; 13 Eyes, fronto-dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/183478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[1031,1063,512,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="13.0">13</number>
</figureCitation>
). Chelicera with 
<number box="[1270,1285,512,538]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="3.0">3</number>
promarginal and 
<number box="[205,219,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.0">2</number>
retromarginal teeth. Legs normal length (I 
<number box="[756,811,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="5.5">5.50</number>
; II 
<number box="[858,913,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.8">4.80</number>
; III 
<number box="[970,1025,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="4.5">4.50</number>
; IV 
<number box="[1084,1137,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="5.95">5.95</number>
) (
<number box="[1168,1181,554,580]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.0">1</number>
st leg/dorsal shield of prosoma = 
<number box="[283,339,594,620]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2.9">2.90</number>
). Epigynum without teeth; atrium small, length and width subequal; atrial scape distinct, situated on posterior atrial edge; copulatory ducts large, anteriorly originating, extending and folding posteriorly semi-circular; spermathecae small, widely separated; spermathecal heads long, extending posteriorly, covered mostly by copulatory ducts and only their distal parts visible from dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[1083,1205,714,740]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 9 – 10" captionStart-1="FIGURES 11 – 13" captionStartId-0="6.[151,269,623,647]" captionStartId-1="6.[151,269,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox-0="[241,1355,186,586]" captionTargetBox-1="[201,1434,722,1068]" captionTargetId-0="figure@6.[218,1370,156,600]" captionTargetId-1="figure@6.[151,1436,722,1068]" captionTargetPageId-0="6" captionTargetPageId-1="6" captionText-0="FIGURES 9 – 10. Notiocoelotes lingulatus sp. nov., holotype female from Diaoluoshan Mt., Hainan, China. 9 Epigynum, ventral view; 10 Vulva, dorsal view." captionText-1="FIGURES 11 – 13. Notiocoelotes lingulatus sp. nov., holotype female from Diaoluoshan Mt., Hainan, China. 11 Epigynum, ventral view; 12 Vulva, dorsal view; 13 Eyes, fronto-dorsal view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/183477/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/183478/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Figs 
<number box="[1142,1205,714,740]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="10.5" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="9.0">9–12</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
